<paragraph id="8BE5FB4F1012FFA7FF51FEE57CE45536" blockId="5.[136,1452,264,642]" box="[136,1194,264,291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FF51FEE5796B5537" bold="true" box="[136,293,264,290]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<typeStatus id="54E145ED1012FFA7FF51FEE5788D5537" box="[136,195,264,290]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<treatmentCitation id="0AFBDD5E1012FFA7FEF5FEE57CE85536" author="Eidam" box="[300,1190,264,291]" journal="Beitrage zur Biologie der Pflanzen" page="194" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" score="42.36806585947801" volume="4" year="1886">
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FEF5FEE57AAB5537" authority="Eidam, Beitrage" authorityName="Eidam, Beitrage" box="[300,741,264,290]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="ranarum">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FEF5FEE57A665537" box="[300,552,264,290]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Basidiobolus ranarum</emphasis>
Eidam, Beiträge
</taxonomicName>
zur Biologie der Pflanzen4: 194 (1886)
</treatmentCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5FB4F1012FFA7FF64FEC67B265697" blockId="5.[136,1452,264,642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FF64FEC679475550" bold="true" box="[189,265,299,325]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Notes:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FED6FEC679EF5550" box="[271,417,299,325]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FED6FEC679EF5550" box="[271,417,299,325]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Basidiobolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced by Eidam, with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FCDAFEC17BCC5550" box="[771,898,300,325]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="ranarum">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FCDAFEC17BCC5550" box="[771,898,300,325]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">B. ranarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus id="54E145ED1012FFA7FC15FEC17BB25553" box="[972,1020,300,326]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FB86FEC67CA55553" author="Eidam, E." box="[1119,1259,299,326]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="181 - 251" refId="ref9970" refString="Eidam, E. (1886) Basidiobolus, eine neue Gattung der Entomophthoraeeen. Beitrage zur Biologie der Pflanzen 4: 181 - 251." type="journal article" year="1886">Eidam 1886</bibRefCitation>
). The zygospores are characterized as smooth and thick-walled, globose to subglose, with distinct conjugation beak (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FADEFEA37DD1557C" author="Burkitt, D. P. &amp; Wilson, A. M. M. &amp; Jelliffe, D. B." box="[1287,1439,334,361]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="1669 - 1672" refId="ref8875" refString="Burkitt, D. P., Wilson, A. M. M. &amp; Jelliffe, D. B. (1964) Subcutaneous phycomycosis: A review of 31 cases seen in Uganda. British Medical Journal 1: 1669 - 1672. https: // doi. org / 10.1136 / bmj. 1.5399. 1669" type="journal article" year="1964">Burkitt 1964</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FF51FE9C791D5599" box="[136,339,369,396]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FF51FE9C7954559E" box="[136,282,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Basidiobolus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FE49FE9C7A2E5599" box="[400,608,369,396]" class="Entomophthoromycetes" family="Ancylistaceae" genus="Conidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Entomophthorales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Entomophthoromycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FE49FE9C7A69559E" box="[400,551,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Conidiobolus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
have been reported as human pathogens in the order 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FB0EFE9C7DE9559E" box="[1239,1447,369,395]" class="Entomophthoromycetes" kingdom="Fungi" order="Entomophthorales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Entomophthoromycota" rank="order">Entomophthorales</taxonomicName>
, and their zygospores differ by the presence or absence of conjugation beaks (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FBDCFE787C8155BA" author="Ribes, J. A. &amp; Vanover-Sams, C. L. &amp; Baker, D. J." box="[1029,1231,405,431]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="236 - 301" refId="ref13842" refString="Ribes, J. A., Vanover-Sams, C. L. &amp; Baker, D. J. (2000) Zygomycetes in human disease. Clinical microbiology reviews 13: 236 - 301. https: // doi. org / 10.1128 / CMR. 13.2.236" type="journal article" year="2000">
Ribes 
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FB89FE787CC555BA" box="[1104,1163,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">et al.</emphasis>
2000
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FB05FE787DD155BA" author="Yang, X. &amp; Li, Y. &amp; Zhou, X. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Geng, S. &amp; Liu, H. &amp; Yang, Q. &amp; Liu, X. &amp; Hiruma, M. &amp; Sugita, T. &amp; Ikeda, S. &amp; Ogawa, H." box="[1244,1439,405,431]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="369 - 373" refId="ref15495" refString="Yang, X., Li, Y., Zhou, X., Wang, Y., Geng, S., Liu, H., Yang, Q., Liu, X., Hiruma, M., Sugita, T., Ikeda, S. &amp; Ogawa, H. (2021) Rhinofacial conidiobolomycosis caused by Conidiobolus coronatus in a Chinese rice farmer. Mycoses 53: 369 - 373. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0507.2009.01716. x" type="journal article" year="2021">
Yang 
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FAC6FE787D1455BA" box="[1311,1370,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FF51FE5579CD55C7" box="[136,387,440,466]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="ranarum">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FF51FE5579CD55C7" box="[136,387,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Basidiobolus ranarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can cause Zygomycosis to humans, and clinic symptoms include forming the firm and painless subcutaneous swellings on the trunk and extremities (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FD0DFE367BAA55E0" author="Vilela, R. &amp; Mendoza, L." box="[724,996,475,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" refId="ref15071" refString="Vilela, R. &amp; Mendoza, L. (2018) Human pathogenic entomophthorales. Clinical microbiology reviews 31: e 00014 - 18. https: // doi. org / 10.1128 / CMR. 00014 - 18" type="journal volume" year="2018">Vilela &amp; Mendoza 2018</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A80CC1012FFA7FBA0FE367D7155E3" box="[1145,1343,475,502]" family="Basidiobolaceae" genus="Basidiobolus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Basidiobolales" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Zygomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FBA0FE367D4555E0" box="[1145,1291,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Basidiobolus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
have also caused diseases in horses and dogs (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB86BE1012FFA7FDF9FE137ABD560C" author="Owens, W. R. &amp; Miller, R. I. &amp; Haynes, P. F. &amp; Snider, T. G." box="[544,755,510,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" pagination="703 - 705" refId="ref13561" refString="Owens, W. R., Miller, R. I., Haynes, P. F. &amp; Snider, T. G. (1985) Phycomycosis caused by Basidiobolus haptosporus in two horses. Journal of the American Veterinary Medical Association 186: 703 - 705." type="journal article" year="1985">
Owens 
<emphasis id="B92E275D1012FFA7FDAEFE127AFE560D" box="[631,688,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">et al.</emphasis>
1985
</bibRefCitation>
, 
